# 📚 H2 Economics Case Study Feedback Assistant

An interactive web app for Singapore H2 Economics students to practice past-year style case study questions, receive automated concept-matching feedback, and compare with examiner model answers.

## ✨ Features
- 📖 Scrollable case extracts & data tables
- ✍️ Dedicated text fields per question
- 🤖 Instant automated grading based on official mark scheme keywords
- 📊 Detailed feedback: marks awarded, concepts hit/missed
- 📖 Expandable model answers & examiner notes
- 📱 Fully responsive & mobile-friendly

## 🚀 Quick Start
1. Clone or download this repository
2. Open `index.html` in any modern browser (no server required)
3. Type answers, click **Submit**, and review feedback

## 🌐 Deploy to GitHub Pages
1. Push this repo to GitHub
2. Go to **Settings → Pages**
3. Set source to `Deploy from a branch` → `main` → `/ (root)`
4. Click **Save**. Your app will be live at `https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/`

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- Vanilla HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)
- Zero dependencies. No build step. Optimized for GitHub Pages.

## 📝 Notes for Teachers
- The grading engine uses keyword/concept matching. It's designed as a **formative self-assessment tool**, not a replacement for human marking.
- Students are encouraged to focus on economic reasoning, application to extracts, and precise terminology.
- You can easily update `js/data.js` to add new questions, adjust rubrics, or change extracts.

